the Objective C language has the following class
NSNotificationCenter, which is likely an observer pattern implementation.

https://developer.apple.com/documentation/foundation/nsnotificationcenter
https://developer.apple.com/documentation/foundation/nsnotificationcenter/1415360-addobserver?language=objc

Instance Method
addObserver:selector:name:object:

Adds an entry to the notification center's dispatch table with an observer and a notification selector, and an optional notification name and sender.

Declaration

- (void)addObserver:(id)observer
           selector:(SEL)aSelector
               name:(NSNotificationName)aName
             object:(id)anObject;

